column7:
Tried for around 6hrs outdoor.. can withstand the ridiculous weather pretty well. Face remain matt and not oily. Bought beige (using 21 for laneige cushion) and color was ok.. can try ivory should be brighter. Coverage good for pores but not scars or freckles..The second picture is after I'd gone out for lunch and walked home, and as you can see, I'm quite an oil slick. That said, I didn't put primer, just sunblock, and I didn't set with a powder. I only applied this, drew my brows, eyeliner, blusher, and lipgloss because I wanted to test how it'll hold up. The coverage for this is sheer. Very sheer. You'll need a concealer for your undereye circles, redness around your nose, any zits. It does hide pores really well; I've got massive pores around my nose area, and it blurred them out beautifully. I chose Beige, and even then the colour is a little pale for me (I'm an NC25 for MAC products). After you leave it on your skin for a bit, it dries to a nice non-sticky finish, so technically you don't need to set it with powder. But, given how my lunch-time escapade turned out, I don't think that's a possibility for me. Get it if you're looking for a lightweight foundation with sheer coverage to help blur out your pores. Don't get it if you need heavier coverage and a matte finish in one product.I seriously had a big expectation of this product. This is my 2nd time purchased.
At first, when applied it doesn't feel sticky on my oily face. Light weight on the skin, long-lasting power is awesome & easy to apply.
More important that is really all-day oil control. If you have normal-oily skin and are looking for a cushion to try, definitely check this one out!I tried product. At noon, my face remains flawless, without additional production of facial oil. Recommended for oily skin.Very fast delivery. Hvnt tried the product hope its good. column98:
One of the nicest place to eat Korean Fried Chicken.We have frequent chicken up a few times now. Both at jurong east and parkway parade outlet. Service is impeccable. The staff truly cares for ur satisfaction. 
Ate the buffet at jurong east outlet. It took sometime for our food to arrive as it gets busy during dinner but it's worth the wait. Be patient. The staff are all running around attending to customers and the cooks in the kitchen are doing their best as its cooked to order. Their chicken are of good sized (bigger than other Korean chicken place) and it's crispy and the sauces are all yummy licking good. The bone falls off the meat easily. The popcorn chicken is succulent and moist. The fries amazing. All came piping hot so u have to be patient again when eating. I will always give them 5 stars for food quality and service. It can be expensive without promotion but it's well worth it.the dumplings were great, as was the soya sauce (gangjang) chicken. the sweet and sour (yangnyum) coat was not my cup of tea - in fact, it left me yearning for a cup of tea to wash down its overwhelming flavour. i was pleasantly surprised by the generous portions. most outlets split the drumstick and wing as 2 separate pieces, but here it's billed as a single piece.
kimchi fries were served with a generous topping of sliced chicken that was frankly, quite redundant. granted the restaurant is called Chicken Up, but i could barely taste the kimchi with all the extra sauces and toppings vying for my tastebuds' attention. the smarter option is to keep it simple. after all, we're just looking to even out the protein with some plain, humble potato.
for the most part, i can't complain. great deal, speedy service, a decent offering of sides.Food is delicious, worth if u can eat alot.The staffs are nice & place is clean & neat . buffet is decent too. Waiting time for the food is just nice. Will visit again for sure.
